The Edo State Governor, Mr Godwin Obaseki, has urged businesses and investors in the United Arab Emirates to leverage the reforms initiated by Edo State and invest in the state. He disclosed this while visiting the Nigerian pavilion at the Dubai Expo 2020. During the tour of the pavilion, Obaseki appreciated the infusion of the rich cultural heritage of the Edo people and the display of sculptures and artworks from the Benin Kingdom at the Expo. He also interacted with Nigerian officials as well as prospective investors and businesses from the UAE, highlighting investment opportunities in different sectors of Edo’s economy. Obaseki stated that his administration has recorded huge success in opening up the space for investment through pragmatic reforms in the state’s industrial corridors, infrastructure, education, healthcare, and security.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com